<br /><br />
<br />
<br /><br />
I know the deck is really big but I have many cycling cards. Delving, Cast It Into Fire, Gwemegil, and Arwen Elven Rider. I usually use her text for archery wounds or against little minions to be sure Frodo wont be overwhelm. And Grishnackh, Eye of Sauron and Orc Runner. <br />
<br /><br />
<br />
<br /><br />
I use Gimli, UG and Lego, EC , Saelbeth and Golradir to make it easier for Dwarf of Elfs to win skirmishes so I can use Ancient Enmity and Nobody Tosses a Dwarf + Dwarven Axe. I put the second axe on Fror or Farin depending what is shadow side. Then, the other companions if jsut there to suck up some wounds or I even dont play it depending what is the shadow side. Many others elvens guys for Far-seeing Eyes to discard even more cards. Elven bow to do some wound and be albe to use White Arrows of Lorien. <br />
<br /><br />
<br />
<br /><br />
Shadow side use the same strategy, discards opposants cards and make me draw some cards. I use burden corruption strategy too with Desparate Defence of The Ring, Enduring Evil, Thin And Streched, Gleaming In The Snow, Grishnackh. With that, my Enquea is really usefull and, I usually wait to get 2 Enduring Evil and kill a big guys. Grima, W, can be usefull with Desparate Defense of The Ring. With the burden strategy, my Eye of Sauron become really usefull and I&#39;ve put Taskmaster to be able to get more pool or to have someone to exert depending what I have to do.    <br />
<br /><br />
<br />
<br /><br />
<br />
<br /><br />
*****For Frodo, CH, It&#39;s a little problem, not a big one since Im FP side discards cards too. ALOT of cards.<br />
<br /><br />
Here the statd for FP side:<br />
<br /><br />
Discard 24 cards + White arrow that when I exert I can discard 2, and Dwarven Axe that I have to win a skirmish to remove a cards and Far-Seeing Eyes that I have to play an elf (I have 10 elfs) So Usually I can easly discards 30-40 cards during a game only with my FP side. So his shadow and FP side wont be albe to set up correctly. AND With minion side I can go for corruption too since Desparate Defence of The Ring will work really great :) <br />
<br /><br />
